item.title: A Warning - You may want to check this out for yourslef
item.dc:creator: @davidi2 Davidi2
item.description:
@davidi2 wrote:

While yes, it is a warning, you will get errors (wont run) when trying to run a jdk7 compiled class on a jre6 machine.

A lot of machines (especially older version unix machines that dont have extremely easy ways to update without adding new repos) may still be using jre 6 (openjdk 6). I’ve experienced this problem first hand when running servers on older versions of ubuntu vps’s, having to manually install jre7
